      Having survived until modern times, the Institute has shifted the rules. They now also accept human allies and more troubled sorts while still operating on their base principle: creating a safe haven for the otherwordly. Unfortunately, while students, faculty, and members of the town around them are able to live their lives out in peace, certain members of the administration suffer from the same problems of desire, corruption, and lust for power as humans do, and it brings the question: How long can something like this truly last?
